channel.title: Compiling
channel.description:
I need help with my compilier... when i click compile it shows up this....Welcome and thanks for compiling the UNIX Tony-Scape Client! Note: Remember the rule if you get 100 errors ECHO is off. You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load. The system cannot find the path specified. Compiling Finished. Press any key to continue . . .
But then when i click runclient.bat it doesn't do anything please help me!

item.title: Compiling
item.dc:creator: @Unknown_Supreme Unknown Supreme
item.description:
@Unknown_Supreme wrote:

Wrong section, this needs to be moved to this topic: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,349078.0.html

But I guess I can answer your question real quick… Right click the file and click edit, then change whatever the path is to what yours is. So for example if it says C:/Program Files/Java/jdk1_01 then you want to make sure that is where your java file is.

Have anymore problems? add my msn: icedhott@hotmail.com
